# {{project.name}} - Role & Permission Matrix

> Role definitions, permission mappings, and access levels for {{project.full_name}}.
> **Structured data** is in companion JSONL files for efficient lookups.

## Data Files

| File | Contains | Format |
|------|----------|--------|
| [roles.jsonl](roles.jsonl) | All roles with descriptions and categories | JSONL |
| [permissions.jsonl](permissions.jsonl) | All permissions with descriptions | JSONL |
| [role_permissions.jsonl](role_permissions.jsonl) | Role-to-permission mappings | JSONL |

## Access Levels

| Level | Description | Example |
|-------|-------------|---------|
| **Full Access** | Create, read, update, delete | Admin users |
| **Read/Write** | Create, read, update (no delete) | Editors |
| **Read Only** | View data only | Viewers |
| **No Access** | Cannot access feature | Unauthorized users |

## How to Query

To check if a role has a permission, search `role_permissions.jsonl`:
```
grep "ROLE_CODE" .ai/context/role_permissions.jsonl
```

> **Note**: Populate the JSONL files using the `@Setup-Wizard` agent or manually.
> See JSONL format examples in each file.
